# Material Master VFX - Base Material for All Visual Effects
# Transpersonal Game Studio - VFX Agent #17

## MATERIAL SETUP

Material Domain: Surface
Blend Mode: Translucent
Shading Model: Unlit (para a maioria dos VFX)
Two Sided: True

## MAIN TEXTURE INPUTS

### Base Color Network
- TextureSample: T_VFX_Diffuse (conectar a Texture Object parameter)
- Multiply por Color parameter "TintColor" (default: 1,1,1,1)
- Multiply por Scalar parameter "Brightness" (default: 1.0)

### Alpha/Opacity Network
- TextureSample: T_VFX_Alpha (usar canal R ou Alpha da diffuse)
- Multiply por Scalar parameter "OpacityMultiplier" (default: 1.0)
- Multiply por Vertex Color Alpha (para fade por distância)

### Emissive Network (para efeitos luminosos)
- Base Color output multiplicado por Scalar parameter "EmissiveStrength" (default: 0.0)
- Add com Color parameter "EmissiveColor" (default: 0,0,0,1)

## ANIMATION PARAMETERS

### UV Animation
- Time node conectado a Panner para scroll UV
- Scalar parameters: "ScrollSpeedU" e "ScrollSpeedV" (default: 0.0)
- Add com TexCoord[0] para offset base

### Rotation Animation
- Time node conectado a Rotator
- Scalar parameter: "RotationSpeed" (default: 0.0)
- CenterPoint parameter para pivot: "RotationCenter" (default: 0.5, 0.5)

### Pulsing/Breathing
- Sine wave usando Time input
- Scalar parameters: "PulseSpeed" (default: 1.0) e "PulseIntensity" (default: 0.0)
- Multiply com Opacity ou Emissive

## DISTORTION (para efeitos de calor/energia)

### Heat Distortion Network
- TextureSample: T_VFX_Normal (normal map para distortion)
- Multiply por Scalar parameter "DistortionStrength" (default: 0.0)
- ComponentMask (RG) para Screen Position offset
- Conectar ao Scene Texture:PostProcessInput0

## VERTEX OFFSET (para movimento de partículas)

### Wind Effect
- World Position offset usando Noise texture
- Scalar parameters: "WindStrength" (default: 0.0)
- Vector parameter: "WindDirection" (default: 1,0,0)
- Time-based animation para movimento contínuo

## FRESNEL EFFECTS

### Edge Highlighting
- Fresnel node com Exponent parameter "FresnelPower" (default: 1.0)
- Multiply por Color parameter "FresnelColor" (default: 1,1,1,1)
- Add ao Emissive network

## DEPTH FADE

### Soft Particle Implementation
- DepthFade node com Distance parameter "FadeDistance" (default: 100.0)
- Multiply com final Opacity
- Evita hard edges quando partículas intersectam geometria

## LOD SYSTEM INTEGRATION

### Distance-Based LOD
- CameraPosition distance calculation
- If statements para diferentes níveis de detalhe:
  - LOD0 (0-500): Full complexity
  - LOD1 (500-1500): Reduced texture resolution, simplified effects
  - LOD2 (1500+): Billboard-only, minimal effects

### Performance Switches
- Static Switch parameters para features:
  - "EnableDistortion" (default: True)
  - "EnableAnimation" (default: True)
  - "EnableEmissive" (default: True)
  - "EnableVertexOffset" (default: False)

## PARAMETER GROUPS

### Primary Controls
- TintColor (Color)
- Brightness (Scalar, 0-5)
- OpacityMultiplier (Scalar, 0-2)

### Animation Controls
- ScrollSpeedU/V (Scalar, -5 to 5)
- RotationSpeed (Scalar, -10 to 10)
- PulseSpeed (Scalar, 0-10)
- PulseIntensity (Scalar, 0-1)

### Advanced Controls
- DistortionStrength (Scalar, 0-1)
- WindStrength (Scalar, 0-100)
- WindDirection (Vector)
- FresnelPower (Scalar, 0.1-10)
- FadeDistance (Scalar, 10-1000)

## MATERIAL INSTANCES TEMPLATE

### Instance Naming Convention
MI_VFX_[EffectType]_[Variant]
Exemplos:
- MI_VFX_Dust_Brown
- MI_VFX_Blood_Fresh
- MI_VFX_Spark_Electric
- MI_VFX_Smoke_Dense

### Common Presets
1. **Dust/Dirt Effects**
   - TintColor: (0.8, 0.6, 0.4, 1)
   - Brightness: 0.7
   - OpacityMultiplier: 0.6

2. **Blood Effects**
   - TintColor: (0.6, 0.1, 0.1, 1)
   - Brightness: 0.8
   - EmissiveStrength: 0.2

3. **Energy/Magic Effects**
   - EmissiveStrength: 2.0
   - FresnelPower: 3.0
   - PulseIntensity: 0.5

4. **Atmospheric Effects**
   - OpacityMultiplier: 0.3
   - FadeDistance: 500
   - WindStrength: 20

## PERFORMANCE NOTES

### Optimization Guidelines
- Sempre usar Material Instances, nunca modificar o Master diretamente
- Desabilitar features não utilizadas via Static Switches
- Usar texturas DXT1/DXT5 comprimidas
- Evitar complex math operations em pixel shader quando possível

### Mobile Considerations
- Reduzir instruction count para <100
- Evitar Distortion effects em mobile
- Usar simplified Fresnel calculations
- Limit texture samples para <4 por material

## INTEGRATION POINTS

### Niagara Integration
- All parameters exposed como User Parameters
- Material deve ser compatível com GPU Sprites
- Support para Mesh Renderers quando necessário

### Blueprint Integration
- Dynamic Material Instance creation
- Parameter animation via Timeline
- Event-driven effect triggering

